Pre-Game Insights: Spain and Germany will face each other in the quarterfinals of UEFA Euro 2024.
The last encounter between Spain and Germany in an international tournament ended in a draw during the 2022 World Cup.
Spain's coach expressed confidence in his team, stating, 'We have the best team at this tournament,' while acknowledging Germany's threat.
Spain is expected to line up the same team that played against Georgia in the round of 16.
Germany's Florian Wirtz may come back into the eleven for Leroy Sane, and Jonathan Tah will return after a suspension.
Spain is slightly favored to win despite playing at Germany's home ground.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match will be played at MHPArena in Stuttgart and is expected to kick off at 1200 hrs ET/ 9hrs PST on July 5th, 2024.
Fans can watch the game live on Fox Sports and stream it on Fubo TV and VIX.
